Maintainer: Salma Dewi Nataya <salmadewinataya@mail.ugm.ac.id>
Description: The `sampl3s` package provides a suite of functions for designing,
    selecting, and analyzing samples from populations. It includes methods for
    calculating required sample sizes, performing various sampling techniques 
    (random, stratified, cluster, systematic), and estimating population 
    parameters from sample data. Additional features include margin of error 
    calculation, sample frame validation, and visualization of sampling methods.
    The package is designed to facilitate efficient and reproducible sampling 
    workflows in data analysis.
